transactions.report: Alice, a 32-year-old female, was admitted on May 28, 2023, with complaints of persistent cough, shortness of breath, and fever. She has a medical history of asthma and seasonal allergies. On examination, decreased breath sounds were noted in the lower right lung field. Laboratory tests revealed an elevated white blood cell count and C-reactive protein levels. Chest X-ray showed consolidation in the right lower lobe. Based on the clinical presentation and diagnostic findings, a diagnosis of community-acquired pneumonia was made. The patient was started on appropriate antibiotics and received nebulized bronchodilators and supplemental oxygen for symptom relief. Over the course of her hospital stay, her symptoms gradually improved, and repeat chest X-ray showed resolution of the consolidation. She was discharged on June 1, 2023, with a prescription for oral antibiotics and instructions for follow-up with her primary care physician.
